<article  class="post-179416 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-ux-design post">

	<h2><a href="http://uxdesign.smashingmagazine.com/2014/01/08/lean-ux-manifesto-principle-driven-design/" rel="bookmark" title="Read 'The Lean UX Manifesto: Principle-Driven Design'">The Lean UX Manifesto: Principle-Driven Design</a></h2>

<ul class="postmetadata clearfix">
    <li class="author">By <a rel="author" href="http://uxdesign.smashingmagazine.com/author/anthony-viviano/?rel=author" title="Posts by Anthony Viviano" >Anthony Viviano</a></li>
    <li id="logoedtarget" class="inline"></li>    <li class="date">January 8th, 2014</li>
    <li class="tags"><a href="http://uxdesign.smashingmagazine.com/tag/usability/">Usability</a>, <a href="http://uxdesign.smashingmagazine.com/tag/user-experience/">User Experience</a></li>            <li class="comments"><a href="http://uxdesign.smashingmagazine.com/2014/01/08/lean-ux-manifesto-principle-driven-design/#comments" title="The Lean UX Manifesto: Principle-Driven Design">30 Comments</a></li>
        </ul>

  <p>My colleague Ajay and I have been working at incorporating lean UX at the enterprise level for over two years. In studying it, I find that there’s a temptation to lay down rules, and if the rules aren’t followed... well, then, you can’t call it lean UX. At the end of the day, though, some lean UX is better than none.</p>

<p><a href="http://uxdesign.smashingmagazine.com/2014/01/08/lean-ux-manifesto-principle-driven-design/"><img src="http://media.smashingmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/ux-discussion.jpg" alt="The Lean UX Manifesto: Principle-Driven Design" title="The Lean UX Manifesto: Principle-Driven Design" width="500" height="310"  /></a></p>

<p><strong>"You’re not practicing lean UX if…"</strong> If you were told to finish off the following sentence, how would you do it? I asked that very same question on Twitter, LinkedIn and email to some lean UX thinkers out there. My personal conclusion is simple. Lean UX is a set of principles that may be used to guide you to better, more desirable solutions for users. It’s not a process in which each tool is rigidly applied.</p>
  <a href="http://uxdesign.smashingmagazine.com/2014/01/08/lean-ux-manifesto-principle-driven-design/" class="continue-reading">Read more...</a>

</article>

    
    
<article  class="post-179336 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-events tag-the-smashing-newsletter post">

	<h2><a href="http://www.smashingmagazine.com/smashing-newsletter-issue-100/" rel="bookmark" title="Read 'Smashing Newsletter #100: Here&#8217;s To Another Hundred Issues!'">Smashing Newsletter #100: Here&#8217;s To Another Hundred Issues!</a></h2>

<ul class="postmetadata clearfix">
    <li class="author">By <a rel="author" href="http://www.smashingmagazine.com/author/newsletter-team/?rel=author" title="Posts by Smashing Newsletter Team" >Smashing Newsletter Team</a></li>
        <li class="date">January 7th, 2014</li>
                <li class="comments"><a href="http://www.smashingmagazine.com/smashing-newsletter-issue-100/#comments" title="Smashing Newsletter #100: Here&#8217;s To Another Hundred Issues!"></a></li>
        </ul>

  <p>100 newsletter issues, twice every month, published and sent out tirelessly over the last four years. <strong>What started as a humble little project back in 2010</strong> is now a part of our editorial, a part that we wouldn't want to miss. Finding and featuring all these little side projects, techniques, resources and crazy ideas is so rewarding and so much fun, so of course we're just getting started!</p>

<p><a href="http://www.smashingmagazine.com/smashing-newsletter-issue-100/"><img src="http://media.smashingmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/smashingconf-ny-2014-opt.png" width="450" height="332" alt="Editorial" border="0" style="border-radius: 8px;"/></a></p>

<p>This is going to be quite a year. We've got many surprises coming your way in the next few months, but we never said it wasn't going to be fun. Keep that cup of coffee or tea ready every second Tuesday and  <a href="http://www.smashingmagazine.com/the-smashing-newsletter/">stay tuned with the Smashing Newsletter</a>, folks! ;-)</p>
  <a href="http://www.smashingmagazine.com/smashing-newsletter-issue-100/" class="continue-reading">Read more...</a>

</article>

    
